It got kind of crazy with the
owner because Linda started
renting out spaces. Jeanette
Ingberman had a space, some
radio program had a space.
The landlord thought he was
only renting to Linda, and he
pointed this out to her.
Horace Brockington, JAM volunteer, art historian, and curator

Linda really became a kind
of resource for people,
particularly when she moved
to Broadway. I got the
impression that if you had a
good idea, Linda would help you
realize it.
Lowery Stokes Sims, JAM volunteer, art historian, and curator
